body:
The standard "formula" for a generic swap is:

```c++
...
{
    using std::swap;
    swap(a, b);
}
...
```

Not sure what the problem is, but maybe that's worth trying.

> The standard "formula" for a generic swap is:
> 
> ```c++
> ...
